Nollywood Actress, Lilian Afegbai has denied the claims that her mother, Carol Onyekachi Afegbai killed Momodu Ibrahim, a student of the University of Benin (UNIBEN) in May 2013. DAILY POST had reported that Nigerians are accusing Carol, a senior police officer of killing Momodu Ibrahim, a student of the University of Benin (UNIBEN) in May 2013. They also called on the federal government and the Nigeria Police to arrest and probe Carol. Reacting, Lilian in a post via her Instagram account on Saturday said her mother who is now retired did not kill anyone. According to her, the police officer, Amadin Idahosa who shot the deceased is currently serving his jail at Oko prison in Benin after being sentenced to life improvement by Justice R. Irele-Ifijeh. “My spirit will not be dampened by the death threats and cyber bullying. “I am a Nigerian youth and we deserve a better Nigeria and I will continually fight until it is fixed. “As per my mother being dragged for murder, to the best of my knowledge my mother who is now retired did not kill anyone. “The police officer, Amadin Idahosa that was attached to my mother’s station who killed the suspect was sentenced to life imprisonment by Justice R.Irele -Ifijeh of the High court of Justice Edo state in charge No: B/CD/24C/2014 “He is currently serving his jail term at Oko prison, Benin although he has appealed the matter ip to Supreme Court,” she said. See pictures below…<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-849342" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/unnamed-4-2.jpg" alt="" width="1242" height="891" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/unnamed-4-2.jpg 1242w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/unnamed-4-2-300x215.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/unnamed-4-2-1024x735.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px"> <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-849348" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/1